                <h1>Discover the Life and Works of Jane Austen</h1>
                <p>Jane Austen (1775-1817) was an influential English novelist known for her keen observations of social class and romantic fiction. Born in Hampshire, she published works such as "Pride and Prejudice" and "Sense and Sensibility," which explored themes of love, marriage, and individuality. Her wit and irony continue to resonate today.</p>
